#!/bin/bash
cv() { n=$1 b=$2; r=0; bl=${#b}; for ((i=0;i<${#n};i++)); do c=${n:i:1}; for ((j=0;j<bl;j++)); do if [ "$c" = "${b:j:1}" ]; then r=$((r*bl+j)); break; fi; done; done; echo $r; }; dc() { n=$1 b=$2; bl=${#b}; if [ $n -eq 0 ]; then echo "${b:0:1}"; return; fi; r=""; while [ $n -gt 0 ]; do r="${b:n%bl:1}$r"; n=$((n/bl)); done; echo "$r"; }; dc $(( $(cv "$WATER" "water") + $(cv "$STIR" "stir") )) "bestchol"
